HOUSE BILL 429
M3, M4 6lr1221
CF SB 599
By: Delegates Boyce, Charkoudian, Embry, Fair, Feldmark, Healey, Hill,
Kaufman, Lehman, Patterson, Ruth, Woods, Woorman, and Ziegler Ziegler,
Behler, Foley, Jacobs, Holmes, Lewis, Odom, Stein, and T. Morgan
Introduced and read first time: January 22, 2026
Assigned to: Environment and Transportation
Committee Report: Favorable with amendments
House action: Adopted
Read second time: February 26, 2026
CHAPTER ______
1 AN ACT concerning
2 On–Farm Organics and Wasted Food Reduction and Diversion and Recycling
3 Grant Programs Program – Established
4 FOR the purpose of establishing the On–Farm Organics Diversion and Recycling Grant
5 Program in the Department of Agriculture to award grants to eligible entities to
6 develop and implement on–farm organics recycling and compost use, wasted food
7 prevention, and food rescue; establishing the Wasted Food Reduction and Diversion
8 Grant Program and the County Wasted Food Reduction Block Grant Program in the
9 Department of the Environment to award grants and fund certain projects for
10 infrastructure, programs, and education that reduce, rescue, and divert wasted food
11 in the State and certain counties; and generally relating to wasted food reduction
12 and diversion on–farm organics recycling and compost use, wasted food prevention,
13 and food rescue in the State.
14 BY adding to
15 Article – Agriculture
16 Section 2–109
17 Annotated Code of Maryland
18 (2016 Replacement Volume and 2025 Supplement)
19 BY repealing and reenacting, without amendments,
20 Article – Agriculture
21 Section 2–401(a)(1) and (3) and 2–2001(a), (f), and (g)
