8 HOUSE BILL 429
1 (B) BEGINNING JULY 1, 2028, THERE IS A WASTED FOOD REDUCTION AND
2 DIVERSION GRANT PROGRAM IN THE DEPARTMENT.
3 (C) THE PURPOSE OF THE GRANT PROGRAM IS TO AWARD GRANTS
4 ANNUALLY FOR INFRASTRUCTURE, PROGRAMS, AND EDUCATION THAT REDUCE,
5 RESCUE, AND DIVERT WASTED FOOD IN THE STATE.
6 (D) THE DEPARTMENT, IN CONSULTATION WITH THE DEPARTMENT OF
7 AGRICULTURE, SHALL:
8 (1) ADMINISTER THE GRANT PROGRAM; AND
9 (2) IDENTIFY AND APPLY FOR FUNDING FOR THE GRANT PROGRAM.
10 (E) THE FOLLOWING PERSONS ARE ELIGIBLE FOR A GRANT UNDER THE
11 GRANT PROGRAM:
12 (1) A UNIT OF STATE OR LOCAL GOVERNMENT;
13 (2) A LOCAL EDUCATION AGENCY;
14 (3) AN INSTITUTION OF HIGHER EDUCATION AS DEFINED IN § 10–101
15 OF THE EDUCATION ARTICLE;
16 (4) A NONPROFIT ORGANIZATION;
17 (5) A FARMER, AN URBAN FARMER, OR AN URBAN AGRICULTURAL
18 PRODUCER;
19 (6) A BUSINESS IN THE STATE THAT IS IN GOOD STANDING WITH THE
20 STATE DEPARTMENT OF ASSESSMENTS AND TAXATION; AND
21 (7) A CONSORTIUM OF ANY ENTITIES UNDER THIS SUBSECTION.
22 (F) A PROJECT IS ELIGIBLE FOR A GRANT UNDER THE GRANT PROGRAM IF
23 THE PROJECT DEVELOPS, MAINTAINS, OR EXPANDS INFRASTRUCTURE, COLLECTION
24 PROGRAMS, EDUCATION, OR TECHNICAL ASSISTANCE IN THE STATE THAT:
25 (1) REDUCES THE AMOUNT OF WASTED FOOD GENERATED;
26 (2) RESCUES EDIBLE FOOD FOR PURPOSES OF REDISTRIBUTION;

HOUSE BILL 429 9
1 (3) RECOVERS WASTED FOOD AS ANIMAL FEED IF THE FEED IS
