HOUSE BILL 429 11
1 (A) (1) IN THIS SECTION THE FOLLOWING WORDS HAVE THE MEANINGS
2 INDICATED.
3 (2) “GRANT PROGRAM” MEANS THE COUNTY WASTED FOOD
4 REDUCTION BLOCK GRANT PROGRAM.
5 (3) “OVERBURDENED COMMUNITY” HAS THE MEANING STATED IN §
6 1–701 OF THIS ARTICLE.
7 (4) “UNDERSERVED COMMUNITY” HAS THE MEANING STATED IN §
8 1–701 OF THIS ARTICLE.
9 (5) “URBAN AGRICULTURAL PRODUCER” HAS THE MEANING STATED
10 IN § 2–2001 OF THE AGRICULTURE ARTICLE.
11 (6) “URBAN FARMER” HAS THE MEANING STATED IN § 2–401 OF THE
12 AGRICULTURE ARTICLE.
13 (B) BEGINNING JULY 1, 2028, THERE IS A COUNTY WASTED FOOD
14 REDUCTION BLOCK GRANT PROGRAM IN THE DEPARTMENT.
15 (C) (1) THE PURPOSE OF THE GRANT PROGRAM IS TO AWARD GRANTS TO
16 COUNTIES ANNUALLY IN AMOUNTS PROPORTIONAL TO EACH COUNTY’S
17 POPULATION.
18 (2) FUNDS RECEIVED BY A COUNTY UNDER THIS SUBSECTION SHALL
19 FUND PROJECTS TO DEVELOP, MAINTAIN, OR EXPAND INFRASTRUCTURE,
20 PROGRAMS, AND EDUCATION THAT REDUCE, RESCUE, AND DIVERT WASTED FOOD IN
21 THE COUNTY.
22 (D) THE DEPARTMENT, IN CONSULTATION WITH THE DEPARTMENT OF
23 AGRICULTURE, SHALL:
24 (1) ADMINISTER THE GRANT PROGRAM; AND
25 (2) IDENTIFY AND APPLY FOR FUNDING FOR THE GRANT PROGRAM.
26 (E) IN FUNDING PROJECTS UNDER THE GRANT PROGRAM, A COUNTY SHALL
27 PRIORITIZE PROJECTS THAT:
28 (1) PROVIDE DIRECT, MEANINGFUL, AND ASSURED BENEFITS TO THE
29 COMMUNITY;
30 (2) ADDRESS IMPORTANT COMMUNITY NEEDS;

12 HOUSE BILL 429
1 (3) PREVENT, RESCUE, AND DIVERT WASTED FOOD WITHIN A LOCAL
2 COMMUNITY;
3 (4) PLAN TO PRODUCE COMPOST THAT MEETS THE CLASSIFICATION
4 OF “GENERAL USE” UNDER COMAR 15.18.04.05;
5 (5) PLAN TO PRODUCE MINIMALLY CONTAMINATED COMPOST
6 THROUGH:
7 (I) PROCESSING ORGANIC MATERIALS THAT ARE SEPARATED
8 FROM PACKAGING PRIOR TO COLLECTION;
9 (II) NOT USING DEPACKAGERS; AND
10 (III) MEETING THE U.S. COMPOSTING COUNCIL’S SEAL OF
11 TESTING ASSURANCE;
12 (6) SERVE AN OVERBURDENED OR UNDERSERVED COMMUNITY;
13 (7) MINIMIZE NEGATIVE IMPACTS TO THE LOCAL COMMUNITY; AND
14 (8) MAXIMIZE BENEFITS TO THE LOCAL COMMUNITY, INCLUDING:
15 (I) THE CREATION OF JOBS;
16 (II) INCREASING JOB TRAINING; AND
17 (III) INCREASING HIRING AND LEADERSHIP DEVELOPMENT
18 PRACTICES THAT ARE INCLUSIVE AND PROVIDE A LIVING WAGE.
19 SECTION 2. AND BE IT FURTHER ENACTED, That this Act shall take effect
20 October 1, 2026.
